Elastography Ultrasound Analysis¶

This dataset comprises ultrasound measurements of soft tissue tumours from 157 patients.

                   'Age':'age',

                   'M/F':'sex',
                   'Size':'size',
                   'Depth':'depth',
                   'Contrast':'contrast',

                   'Doppler':'doppler',
                   'Classification':'classification',

                   'Colour ':'colour',
                   'Av Strain':'av_strain'})
df['malignant'] = [1 if i == 3 else 0 for i in df.classification]
age_defs = {0:'0-20',1:'21-30',2:'31-40',3:'41-50',4:'51-60',5:'61-70',6:'>70'}
site_defs = {0:'Head/Neck',1:'Upper Torso',2:'Lower Torso',3:'Arm',4:'Leg'}
sex_defs = {0:'Male',1:'Female'}
size_defs = {0:'0-5',1:'6-10',2:'11-20',3:'>20'}
depth_defs = {0:'Superficial',1:'Deep'}
contrast_defs = {0:'Hypo',1:'Iso',2:'Hyper',3:'Complex'}
wall_defs = {0:'Regular',1:'Irregular'}
doppler_defs = {0:'No',1:'Yes'}
classification_defs = {0:'Benign',1:'Malignant',2:'Lipoma',3:'Atypical Lipoma'}
elastography_defs = {0:'Homogenous',1:'Heterogenous'}
colour_defs = {0:'Green_',
              1:'Green/Yellow_',
              2:'Green/Red_',
              3:'Green/Yellow/Blue_',
              4:'Green/Blue_',
              5:'Blue_',
              6:'Green/Black_',
              7:'Green/Blue/Black_',
              8:'Blue/Black_',

av_strain_defs = {0:'0-1',1:'1-5',2:'6-10',3:'>10'}
malignant_defs = {0:'Benign',1:'Malignant'}
df['age'] = [age_defs[i] for i in df['age']]
df['site'] = [site_defs[i] for i in df['site']]

                    Tentative conclusions based on visualisations is that there appear to be some modest relationships between some of the variables. Age and average strain would require more data to be collected in order investigate any relationship further but variables which do seem to have an association with malignancy include: Female sex (OR=2.9) Increased depth (OR=1.8) Anatomical location of leg (OR=) Complex contrast Irregular wall Presence of doppler flow Heterogenous contrast Presence of blue colour

                              classification_performance = {}
full_data_cols = ['age','site','sex','size','depth','contrast','wall','doppler',
                  'elastography','colour','av_strain','bla','blu','gre','re','yel']
low_p_cols = ['contrast','depth','size','wall','doppler','elastography', 'sex', 'site', 'age', 'blu']
custom_cols = ['contrast','elastography','doppler']
contrast_col = ['contrast']

def calc_confusion_matrix(cm):
    c = {}
    try:
        c['accuracy'] = (cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_benign'] + cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_malignant']) / cm.sum().sum()
    except:
        c['accuracy'] = None
    try:
        c['sensitivity'] = (cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_malignant']) / float(cm.loc['actual_malignant'].sum())
    except:
        c['sensitivity'] = None
    try:
        c['specificity'] = (cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_benign']) / float(cm.loc['actual_benign'].sum())
    except:
        c['specificity'] = None
    try:
        c['prop_malignant'] = (cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_malignant'] + cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_malignant']) / cm.sum().sum()
    except:
        c['prop_malignant'] = None
    return c

                              def blr_func(train_cols_arg,model_name):
    train_cols = train_cols_arg
    patsy_string = 'malignant ~ C(' + ') + C('.join(train_cols) + ')'
    y, X = full_data_dmatrices = dmatrices(patsy_string,df)
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = cross_validation.train_test_split(X,y.ravel(),test_size=0.1)
    model = LogisticRegression()
    model.fit(X=X_train, y=y_train)
    predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    cm = pd.DataFrame(columns=['predicted_benign','predicted_malignant'],index=['actual_benign','actual_malignant'])
    cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_benign'] = 0
    cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_malignant'] = 0
    cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_benign'] = 0
    cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_malignant'] = 0
    cm_calc = zip(y_test,predictions)
    for i in cm_calc:
        if(i[0] == 0):
            # actual is benign
            if (i[1] == 0):
                # Predicted is benign
                cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_benign'] += 1
            else:
                # Predicted is malignant
                cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_benign'] += 1
        else:
            #actual is malignant
            if (i[1] == 0):
                # Predicted is benign
                cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_malignant'] += 1
            else:
                # Predicted is malignant
                cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_malignant'] += 1
    c = {}
    c['model_name'] = model_name
    c['model'] = 'logistic'
    c['vars'] = train_cols_arg
    c['accuracy'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['accuracy']
    c['sensitivity'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['sensitivity']
    c['specificity'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['specificity']
    c['prop_malignant'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['prop_malignant']
    classification_performance[model_name] = dict(c)
    return dict(c)

                              Ensemble¶

                              In [16]:
                              def ensemble_func(train_cols_arg,model_name,num_matches_needed):
    train_cols = train_cols_arg
    patsy_string = 'malignant ~ C(' + ') + C('.join(train_cols) + ')'
    y, X = full_data_dmatrices = dmatrices(patsy_string,df)
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = cross_validation.train_test_split(X,y.ravel(),test_size=0.1)
    pred_dict = {}
    pred_dict['actual'] = y_test
    model = LogisticRegression()
    model.fit(X=X_train, y=y_train)
    predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    pred_dict['logistic'] = list(predictions)
    model = RandomForestClassifier()
    model.fit(X=X_train, y=y_train)
    predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    pred_dict['RF'] = list(predictions)
    model = SVC()
    model.fit(X=X_train, y=y_train)
    predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    pred_dict['SVM'] = list(predictions)
    for i in range(len(pred_dict['actual'])):
        num_matches = 0
        if (pred_dict['logistic'][i] == 1):
            num_matches += 1
        if (pred_dict['RF'][i] == 1):
            num_matches += 1
        if (pred_dict['SVM'][i] == 1):
            num_matches += 1
        if (num_matches >= num_matches_needed):
            predictions[i] = 1
        else:
            predictions[i] = 0
    cm = pd.DataFrame(columns=['predicted_benign','predicted_malignant'],index=['actual_benign','actual_malignant'])
    cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_benign'] = 0
    cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_malignant'] = 0
    cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_benign'] = 0
    cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_malignant'] = 0
    cm_calc = zip(y_test,predictions)
    for i in cm_calc:
        if(i[0] == 0):
            # actual is benign
            if (i[1] == 0):
                # Predicted is benign
                cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_benign'] += 1
            else:
                # Predicted is malignant
                cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_benign'] += 1
        else:
            #actual is malignant
            if (i[1] == 0):
                # Predicted is benign
                cm['predicted_benign'].loc['actual_malignant'] += 1
            else:
                # Predicted is malignant
                cm['predicted_malignant'].loc['actual_malignant'] += 1
    c = {}
    c['model_name'] = model_name
    c['model'] = 'ensemble'
    c['vars'] = train_cols_arg
    c['accuracy'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['accuracy']
    c['sensitivity'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['sensitivity']
    c['specificity'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['specificity']
    c['prop_malignant'] = calc_confusion_matrix(cm)['prop_malignant']
    classification_performance[model_name] = dict(c)
    return dict(c)
